OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778227271
OL,3,CLabour could lose more than 50 seats
OL,4,Cin Birmingham, poll suggests
OL,6,FWhilst it might seem surprising that
OL,7,Fthis vote share, with only a 3%
OL,8,Fdifference, has led to a massively
OL,9,Fdifferent outcome for seats, it could
OL,10,Fbe possible in our voting system.
OL,12,FAll local election results will be
OL,13,Fdecided by "first past the post", so
OL,14,Fgetting only one vote more than your
OL,15,Fopponent will win you the seat. Labour
OL,16,Fcould still get 23% of the vote and
OL,17,Fwin only 5% of the seats.
OL,19,FFor context, Keir Starmer's Labour won
OL,20,Fits massive majority at the last
OL,21,Felection on 33% of the vote.
OL,26,@uD@LOUuD@`O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
