PN,37706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778227271
OL,3,CLabour could lose more than 50 seats
OL,4,Cin Birmingham, poll suggests
OL,6,FMassive. If this comes to happen, it
OL,7,Fwill be the biggest shake-up in
OL,8,FBirmingham's political history.
OL,10,FFor the first time ever, Labour and
OL,11,Fthe Tories won't be the two biggest
OL,12,Fparties. Instead, they will be
OL,13,Freplaced by a Reform minority and
OL,14,FIndependent opposition.
OL,16,FThis is not just seismic for Labour -
OL,17,Fit was only in 2007 that the
OL,18,FConservatives spent four years as the
OL,19,Flargest party.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778227271
OL,3,CLabour could lose more than 50 seats
OL,4,Cin Birmingham, poll suggests
OL,6,FYou have to go all the way back to
OL,7,F1996 to find a time the Tories were
OL,8,Fnot at least the second-largest party.
OL,10,FMany previous polls predicted a
OL,11,Ffractured rainbow council with the
OL,12,Fvote split out evenly. But, with our
OL,13,Fvoting system, there is always a
OL,14,Fchance that even a small advantage in
OL,15,Fvote share can produce huge results.
OL,17,FWhether this comes to pass or not, it
OL,18,Fis clear, poll after poll, that a
OL,19,Flarge proportion of Burmmies don't
OL,20,Fwant what traditional politcal
OL,21,Fpowerhouses are offering.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
